PIXTREAM is a Peer-to-Peer Streaming System.

Basic usage:

Run the tracker first:

$ bin/pixtreamtracker

Usage: pixtreamtracker [options]

Options:
  -h, --help                             Show this help message and exit
  -p PORT, --port=PORT                   Listening Port. Default is 8080
  -i INTERVAL, --interval=INTERVAL       Interval in seconds for peers to make
                                         requests

The run one or more peers:

$ bin/pixtreampeer http://localhost:8080

Usage: usage: pixtreampeer [options] tracker_url

Options:
  -h, --help                             Show this help message and exit
  -i ADDRESS, --ip=ADDRESS               IP Address to use
  -p PORT, --port=PORT                   Listening Port. Default is 20000

